    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-03T11:39:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-03T11:39:00-05:00" n="662"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d662">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–354: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">United States Delegation</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d662fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_PDH1"
                            >Popper</persName> of <gloss target="#t_UNA1">UNA</gloss>/<gloss
                            target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>. Repeated to London as telegram 6520 and to
                        Bangkok as telegram 2405.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-03T12:39:00-04:00"
                            >June 3, 1954—12:39 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 334. In future conversations re Thai
                        <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> appeal for <gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss> observation, may be helpful for you to know British have been
                    making strenuous efforts in New York to ensure that Thai request is for <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> observation limited to Thailand alone. British
                    have pressed <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> use influence with Thai
                        <gloss target="#t_Del1">Del</gloss> to restrict opening Thai <gloss
                        target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> statement accordingly. <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                        >USUN</gloss> has refused, stating our position clear from outset <gloss
                        target="#t_POC1">POC</gloss> subcommission must be given authority observe
                    in other states in general area if those states so request, though we would
                    expect Laos and Cambodia would not at this time make such a request. <persName
                        corresp="#p_TK1">Khoman</persName> told <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                        >USUN</gloss> yesterday he could not accept restriction <gloss
                        target="#t_POC1">POC</gloss> subcommission authority to Thailand alone; said
                    public opinion his country would not consider it provided adequate protection
                    for Thailand.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
